The White House Coronavirus Task Force held a meeting at the Department of Education to discuss the reopening of America's schools. Vice President Mike Pence, along with other task force members, provided updates on testing efforts, hospital capacity, and the current state of the pandemic. They emphasized the importance of getting children back to school for their education, mental health, and well-being. They also discussed the CDC guidelines for reopening schools and stated that they are supportive of schools reopening and willing to work with states and local communities to ensure a safe return. The Vice President mentioned that the federal government is ready to provide resources and assistance to help schools reopen, including testing, personal protective equipment, and other supplies. The President's recent tweets about cutting funding for schools that do not reopen were also addressed, with the Vice President stating that they want to provide leadership and incentives to get kids back to school, but decisions will ultimately be made at the state and local level.